  "text": "It is worth noting that the BHPS model was applied, at first, for calculating the intrinsic charm distribution [CITATION_1] . However, Chang and Pang [CITATION_2] generalized it to the light five-quark states to calculate their intrinsic distributions in the proton and also to extract their probabilities (P qq 5 ) using available experimental data. It is interesting to note that they obtained different values for the P dd 5",
